{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JTzA8ZJqihhGA1A1p8D1N1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to: `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.22.txt`\n2. Filename rules:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match main title in content (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. Recipe mix: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n4. Categories: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n5. Mix of single-word and multi-word titles\n\n6. Cannot use existing recipes (given a big list)\n\n7. Pattern requirements:\n   - 5 files with SPILLOVER: Corrupted text from previous recipe (10-50 lines) before actual title, with partial measurements, broken words, garbled text. 40-60 lines total.\n   - 3 files with METADATA_PREFIX: Category or serving info before title. Examples given.\n   - 2 files with SPLIT_TITLE: Title split across 2-4 lines.\n\n8. File length: 15-60 lines (spillover files 40-60 lines)\n\nLet me plan out 10 recipes that aren't in the exclusion list:\n\n**Spillover (5 files - 40-60 lines each):**\n1. Mushroom Risotto\n2. Sweet Potato Salad\n3. Cherry Jam\n4. Fish Tacos\n5. Pumpkin Soup\n\n**Metadata Prefix (3 files):**\n1. Piernik (Polish gingerbread)\n2. Lemon Cheesecake\n3. Vegetable Curry\n\n**Split Title (2 files):**\n1. Baked Tomato Risotto with Basil\n2. Grilled Salmon with Herb Butter\n\n\nNow I need to balance the language distribution. With 10 recipes total, I should aim for 6 English and 4 Polish. Let me adjust: swap out some English recipes for Polish ones like Bigos z Grzybami, Placki Ziemniaczane, and Sernik, while keeping the spillover and metadata patterns intact. I'll avoid any recipes already in the exclusion list and ensure each file has realistic OCR artifacts appropriate to its pattern type. That gives me 7 EN + 3 PL, still one Polish recipe short. I'll swap Cherry Jam for another Polish dish. Kapusniak works well as a traditional cabbage soup to round out the spillover section. Now I have 6 EN + 4 PL across all categories, hitting my target ratio. PL)\n\n**Metadata Prefix (3):**\n1. Sernik z Malinami (PL)\n2. Lemon Cheesecake (EN)\n3. Vegetable Curry (EN)\n\n**Split Title (2):**\n1. Baked Tomato Risotto with Basil (EN)\n2. Grilled Salmon with Herb Butter (EN)\n\nThat gives me 4EN and 3PL, but I need 6EN and 4PL total. I'm still short on English entries. Let me adjust the distribution—I could move some items between sections or swap out a Polish dish for an English one to reach the target counts. 2 English\n1. Paprikash (EN)\n2. Cheesecake z Jeżynami (PL)\n3. Minestrone (EN)\n\n**Split Title (2):** 0 Polish, 2 English\n1. Baked Tomato Risotto with Basil (EN)\n2. Grilled Salmon with Herb Butter (EN)\n\nTotal: 3+2+2 = 7 EN, 2+1+0 = 3 PL. Still need 1 more PL and 1 less EN.\n\nLet me adjust split title to have 1 Polish:\n1. Baked Tomato Risotto with Basil (EN)\n2. Smażone Pierniki (PL)\n\nTotal: 3+2+1 = 6 EN, 2+1+1 = 4 PL. That matches the target.\n\nNow I'll verify none of these recipes appear on the excluded list. Checking each one: Mushroom Risotto, Sweet Potato Salad, Bigos z Grzybami (distinct from the excluded \"Bigos Myśliwski\"), Cherry Jam, Kluski Owocowe, Paprikash, Cheesecake z Jeżynami, Minestrone, Baked Tomato Risotto with Basil, and Smażone Pierniki are all clear. Time to generate the files with OCR artifacts included, starting with SPILLOVER content that spans 10-50 lines.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":75757,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":75757},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_i