{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JTzA8ZJqihhGA1A1p8D1N1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JBNEsPPUgWwScNKZJVKRBY","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Mushroom Risotto.generated.22.txt","content":"Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\ncreamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\nSeason with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n\nCARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n\nSlice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\nlemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n\nPreparation: 10 minutes\nServes: 4\n\nCARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n\nPlace thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\noil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\nthinly sliced radish.\n\nnto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\nwith damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n\nPlace pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n\nMakes: 1 dozen\n\nFRESH PASTA DOUGH\n\n125 grams plain flour\n½ cup plus ı tablespoon water\nPinch of sea salt\n\nCombine flour and slt on work bench. Make well in center. Add water gradually, mixing with fork\nuntil dough comes together. Knead 5 minutes.\n\nMushroom Risotto\n\nIngredients:\n300g arborio rice\n1 liter vegetable stock\n250g mixed mushrooms, sliced\n1 medium onion, finely diced\n100ml dry white wine\n50g butter\n50g parmesan cheese, grated\n2 tablespoons olive oil\nSalt and white pepper to taste\nFresh parsley for garnish\n\nMethod:\nHeat stock in separate pan and keep at gentle simmer. Heat olive oil in large risotto pan over\nmedium heat. Sauté onion until translucent, about 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook until\ngolden, approximately 5 minutes. Add rice and stir constantly for 2 minutes to toast grains.\n\nDeglaze with white wine and stir until absorbed. Begin adding warm stock one ladle at a time,\nstirring frequently. Each addition should be absorbed before adding more stock, taking about\n18-20 minutes total. The rice should be creamy yet retain a slight firmness to the bite.\n\nFinish risotto by stirring in butter and grated parmesan cheese. Season with salt and white\npepper to taste. Transfer to serving bowl and garnish with fresh parsley and additional cheese.\n\nServes: 4-6\nPreparation time: 10 minutes\nCooking time: 30 minutes\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":75757,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":75757},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4939b60-f5d7-4572-ab91-3aec02accfdd","uuid":"8a7d7123-a9b4-40a0-91ea-6640c9d981e2"}
