{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JTzA8ZJqihhGA1A1p8D1N1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JEQkPD96pVX49g8SGps35G","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Sweet Potato Salad.generated.22.txt","content":"2 large sweet potatoes, peeled and cut into 2cm cubes\n4 cups fresh spinach leaves\n½ red onion, thinly sliced\n½ cup roasted walnuts, roughly chopped\n¼ cup dried cranberries\n½ cup crumbled goat cheese or feta\n\nFor dressing:\n3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n1½ tablespoons balsamic vinegar\n1 tablespoon maple syrup\n1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\nMethod:\nPreheat oven to 200°C. Toss sweet potato cubes with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread on\nbaking tray in single layer. Roast for 25-30 minutes until golden and tender, stirring halfway\nthrough cooking time.\n\nWhile potatoes roast, whisk together dressing ingredients in small bowl until emulsified.\nSeason to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.\n\nIn large salad bowl, combine spinach, sliced red onion, and fresh greens. Add roasted sweet\npotatoes while still warm. Drizzle dressing over salad and toss gently to combine. Top with\nwalnuts, cranberries, and crumbled goat cheese.\n\nServe immediately while potatoes are still slightly warm, or chill before serving.\n\nSweet Potato Salad\n\nA vibrant autumn salad combining roasted sweet potato, fresh greens, and warm spices.\n\nIngredients:\n2 large sweet potatoes\n4 cups baby spinach\n½ red onion, finely sliced\n¾ cup candied walnuts\n¼ cup dried cranberries\n¼ cup goat cheese, crumbled\n2 tablespoons pumpkin seeds\n\nDressing:\n¼ cup extra virgin olive oil\n2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar\n½ tablespoon maple syrup\n¼ teaspoon Dijon mustard\nPinch of smoked paprika\nSalt and pepper\n\nPreparation:\nRoast sweet potato cubes at 200°C for 30 minutes until tender. Prepare dressing by whisking\noil, vinegar, maple syrup, and mustard together. Combine spinach and thinly sliced onion in\nlarge bowl. Add warm sweet potatoes, drizzle with dressing, and toss to combine. Finish with\nwalnuts, cranberries, and crumbled cheese.\n\nServes: 4\nTime: 35 minutes\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":75757,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":75757},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4939b60-f5d7-4572-ab91-3aec02accfdd","uuid":"810c5416-f6c7-4f65-9aab-756254b1217b"}
