{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JTzA8ZJqihhGA1A1p8D1N1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01U6DSCfrQ79QUMnSw1XcBFL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Paprikash.generated.22.txt","content":"Dnia | Główne dania\n/ Węgier / Gula\nGOTOWANIE 45 MIN\n\nPaprikash\n\nA rich Hungarian beef stew with paprika, sour cream, and tender vegetables.\n\nIngredients:\n800g beef chuck, cut into 3cm cubes\n3 tablespoons Hungarian paprika\n1 large onion, roughly chopped\n3 cloves garlic, minced\n2 red bell peppers, sliced\n200g mushrooms, quartered\n1 medium carrot, chunked\n400ml beef stock\n200ml sour cream\n2 tablespoons tomato paste\n1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n2 bay leaves\nSalt and pepper to taste\nFresh parsley for garnish\nEgg noodles for serving\n\nMethod:\nHeat oil in heavy pot over medium-high heat. Brown beef in batches, 3-4 minutes per side.\nRemove and set aside. Add chopped onion and garlic, cook until softened, about 3 minutes.\n\nStir in paprika and tomato paste, cook for 1 minute to toast spices. Return beef to pot,\nadd stock, bay leaves, salt, and pepper. Bring to simmer, cover, and cook for 30 minutes.\n\nAdd bell peppers, mushrooms, and carrot. Continue simmering for 15 minutes until vegetables\nare tender and beef is very soft. Remove from heat, stir in sour cream gently.\n\nAdjust seasoning. Serve over cooked egg noodles, garnished with fresh parsley. This stew is\nexcellent made a day ahead and reheated.\n\nServes: 4-6\nPreparation: 15 minutes\nCooking: 45 minutes\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":75757,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":75757},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":nul